				caption: '',
				content: "‘First spokesman of the other tribes’; literally, ‘first among all the house of Joseph’, but the name Joseph is evidently used here, as in several other places, to designate the rest of Israel apart from Juda. Benjamin is here included under ‘Joseph’, although, when the kingdom was divided under Roboam, it remained united to Juda."
			},
					475: {
				id_comment: 475,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "‘My word has been passed’, cf. 16.4 above. David is perhaps interpreting his promise there made, ‘All that was Miphiboseth’s is thine’ as meaning ‘All that was Miphiboseth’s is equally thine’, so that the property would have to be divided between them. David has been criticized for not punishing Siba’s treachery to his master; but it is quite possible that Siba was acting partly in Miphiboseth’s interest, under the impression that Absalom was likely to be victorious—the property which Siba managed for his master (9.10) would be safe from confiscation in either event."
			},
